    • Method Detail

      • isOutsideOfficeHours

        public static boolean isOutsideOfficeHours​(java.time.OffsetTime offsetTime)
        A static method that return whether a given single time lies outside the bounds of the defined office hours of 8 AM-10 PM EST. A time is outside office hours if it is before the starting time or after the ending time. If it is exactly either, then it is within office hours.
        Parameters:
        offsetTime - the time to compare that already has an offset applied that
        Returns:
        whether the given time is outside the defined office hours.
